Sender has ip address of receiver but doesn't have mac address.
Arp helps by mapping the ip address to the physical mac address.

2.ARP is used to map IP addresses to MAC addresses. In Packet Tracer simulation, when PC1 sends a ping to PC2, it first sends an ARP request asking for the MAC address of PC2. PC2 replies with its MAC address, and communication begins.

In ARP spoofing, a malicious device sends a fake ARP reply, claiming to have the IP address of another device. This causes the sender to associate the wrong MAC address with the IP, leading to incorrect data delivery and potential security attacks like man-in-the-middle.

